---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import kim_profile from "./img/kim_profile.jpg";
import mark_profile from "./img/mark_profile.jpg";
import justin_profile from "./img/justin_profile.jpg";
import baskin_img from "./img/baskin.jpg";
import sc_pano from "./img/sc_pano.jpeg";
---

<Layout>
  <div
    style="background-image: url('/img/baskin.jpg'); background-size: cover; padding: 4rem;"
  >
    <p style="padding:2rem;background-color:#f5bd2f; align-self: center;">
      The MuHSiC (Multilingual Hispanic Speech in California) project is a
      robust and linguistically rich corpus of bilingual Spanish-English speech
      samples culled from sociolinguistic interviews and naturalistic
      conversations among speakers of diverse social profiles and regional
      origins throughout the state of California. Speech data were collected by
      a team of undergraduate students trained by graduate students and the 3
      faculty PIs, specifically focusing on familiar acquaintances to maximize
      participantsâ€™ comfort and naturalness during the recording session.
      Comprised of 35-minute recordings in each of Spanish and English from
      California Spanish-English bilinguals, this corpus provides an invaluable
      linguistic resource for language scholars interested in examining the
      phonology, phonetics, morphology, syntax, and lexicon of Spanish-English
      bilinguals in California.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>What We Are</h2>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div>
      <p>
        The Multilingual Hispanic Speech in California Corpus has been made
        possible in part by a <strong
          >Multicampus Research Programs and Initiatives Grant (MRPI Grant
          M23PL5866)</strong
        > awarded to Mark Amengual, Ji Young Kim, and Justin Davidson.
      </p>
      <p>
        Any views, findings, conclusions, or recommendations expressed in this
        website and project, do not necessarily represent those of the
        University of California.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <figure id="login" style="cursor: pointer;">
        <img
          src="https://templatecampuspress.sites.ucsc.edu/files/2024/12/Screen-Shot-2024-11-13-at-2.42.21-PM.png"
          alt=""
